news.title: Frame rules to allot TNHB houses for young lawyers: Madras HC
news.para: The court passed the order on a plea moved by advocate P Subburaj for a direction to the Tamil Nadu Housing Board to allot a house under the public quota for rent at Tower Block, Taylors Road, Kilpauk, Chennai.

news.title: Indore: Court directs police to register fraud case against builder
news.para: The court of judicial magistrate first class Firoz Akhtar directed police to register a case of forgery against builder Dwarikadheesh Agarwal, his wife and two employees Anand Vyas and Nilesh Jaiswal.

news.title: DevX sets up 90,000-sq-ft coworking center in Vadodara
news.para: According to Umesh Uttamchandani, Co-Founder – DevX, the size of the new center is an indication of the company’s optimism on the next wave of growth from tier II cities of Gujarat and India.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 210 units over property tax dues
news.para: So far, the tax department has sealed 1,291 properties in the East Zone under its ongoing drive. The department has also issued notices to 11,658 property owners.

news.title: VMRDA gets approval for its Vizianagaram MIG layouts
news.para: Meanwhile, the VMRDA has also sent proposals to the DTCP to develop two more layouts in 363 acres in Visakhapatnam district. One layout will come up in about 269.3 acres in GS Agraharam and Ramavaram villages, and the other one in Palavalasa (93.8 acres) in the Vizag suburbs.

news.title: Chandigarh: 15,000 houses in colonies set to pay property tax
news.para: The municipal corporation (MC) is going to bring houses in colonies within the tax ambit to fill its depleting coffers in a major move. The houses having an area of 500 square feet or above will have to pay property tax.

news.title: Nagpur: NIT gets 850 applications in first week for Gunthewari 2.0
news.para: TOI had on January 31 highlighted that NIT did not launch Gunthewari 2.0 despite approval from the state government on March 12, 2021, causing loss to lakhs of plot owners and also civic agency. Taking cognisance of TOI reports, NIT started the process to launch the scheme.

news.title: Rajasthan extends land conversion cut-off date to December 31, 2021
news.para: The move is aimed to provide ease to landowners in utilising their land for urbanisation. The amendment is likely to be discussed in the assembly this week.

news.title: UPPCB ask Supertech to mitigate spread of dust from twin towers demolition
news.para: The developer has also been directed to submit regular reports on air and noise pollution as Edifice Engineering, the company entrusted with the job of demolishing the towers, has already started work at the site.

news.title: JetSynthesys' CEO buys century old bungalow in Pune for over Rs 62 crore
news.para: This is the most expensive bungalow deal concluded in Pune ever. The ground plus 1 storey- property is sprawled over 1.25 acre in Koregaon Park's Lane 1, Pune’s emerging billionaire avenue, and is located opposite the Osho Ashram and a proposed bungalow of Rajiv Bajaj.

news.title: Gurugram: NBCC questions DC order to refund Green View residents
news.para: Weeks after the vertical collapse of living rooms claimed two lives at Chintels Paradiso, the residents of NBCC Green View in Sector 37D were asked to vacate by March 1 their flats that were dubbed unsafe for living just four years after being handed over.

news.title: Haryana to conduct structural audit of buildings where complaints received
news.para: To look into the complaints pertaining to such buildings in Haryana, a structural audit will be conducted and a committee of engineers from IIT will be constituted, the minister said.

news.title: SC says no to transferring, clubbing of criminal cases against Amrapali directors
news.para: ​A bench headed by Justice Uday Umesh Lalit did not agree to the fervent submission of the counsel of Shiv Priya, one of the jailed officials of the real estate group, like coal scam cases, the trials in 85 criminal matters, which are of similar nature, can be transferred to one court from seven different courts in the national capital.

news.title: Number one priority is to ensure every Amrapali homebuyer gets flat: SC
news.para: The bench told one of the homebuyers aggrieved by not getting specification of the flat, "For us, our number one priority is that we want a roof for every Amrapali homebuyer. We are not going to get diverted by nitty-gritty."

news.title: China Evergrande Group suspends share trading again
news.para: Among those embroiled in the crisis is Evergrande, one of the country's largest developers, which has been involved in restructuring negotiations after racking up $300 billion in liabilities.
